import pyautogui
import time
import uiautomation as auto

try:
    # Press Windows key to open Start menu
    pyautogui.press('win')
    time.sleep(0.5)
    # Type WhatsApp to search
    pyautogui.write('WhatsApp', interval=0.1)
    time.sleep(0.5)
    # Press Enter to launch
    pyautogui.press('enter')
    time.sleep(2)
    # Verify WhatsApp window appears
    wp = auto.WindowControl(searchDepth=1, ClassName='Chrome_WidgetWin_1')
    if wp.Exists():
        print("EXECUTION_SUCCESS")
    else:
        print("FAILED: WhatsApp window not found")
except Exception as e:
    print(f"FAILED: {e}")
